new.description: This PoC script exploits CVE-2024-39090, a CSRF to Stored XSS vulnerability in PHPGurukul Online Shopping Portal v2.0. It automates CSRF attacks to inject persistent JavaScript payloads, which execute when a privileged user accesses the affected page, enabling actions such as session hijacking or credential theft.

new.name: CVE-2024-9326-PoC
new.description: This PoC script is designed to verify the presence of CVE-2024-9326, a high SQL Injection vulnerability in PHPGurukul Online Shopping Portal v2.0. It automates the exploitation process to determine if the target web application is vulnerable, allowing security professionals to assess and confirm the flaw's existence.
